  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 610 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sesame-mandarin-chicken-salad-619cfde5c27ca873d462d8ea
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
time required: 25 minutes
servings: 2
cuisine: Asian
---

Wash and dry produce.

Zest @mandarin orange{1} until you have ¼ tsp (1⁄3 tsp for 4 servings); peel and
dice fruit into bite-size pieces.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sesame dressing{1.5%ounce}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce},
and mandarin zest. Season with a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a #large nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @cashews{1/2%ounce},
@sugar{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4 servings), and @water{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP water for 4).
Cook, stirring often, until water has evaporated and cashews are coated and
lightly toasted, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a second small bowl. Wipe out pan.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with
@garlic powder{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in pan used for cashews over medium-high
heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes}
per side.

Remove from pan; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

In a #large bowl{}, toss @spinach{5%ounce}, @red cabbage and carrot mix{4%ounce},
and half the mandarin with half the dressing.

Thinly slice chicken crosswise.

Divide salad between #bowls{}. Top with chicken, candied cashews, and remaining
mandarin. Drizzle with remaining dressing and serve.